Afropop singer Yemi Alade has opened up on her earnest wish as her 33rd birthday draws closer. The self-acclaimed ‘Mama Africa’ in a social media post, revealed she desires to improve her act of communication. According to Alade, Nigerians have a great tendency to always turn discussions into arguments which is why she wants to consciously work at being able to communicate her feelings without it resorting to an argument.   I didn’t hit a lady and run away, Timaya reacts     Kanayo makes birthday appeal for Kanu’s release     2022 Headies: I deserve an award, says Portable   The post read: “It’s My Birth Month and I really want to work towards INTENTIONALLY being better at Communicating My Feelings. “There is a thin line between an argument and discussion. Being a typical Nigerian, it’s easy to turn everything into an argument, rather than a discussion. “I want to undo that… Let’s see how that goes…”